'''1776委员会'''（1776 Commission）是第45任美国总统[[唐納·川普|唐納·川普]]于2020年9月成立的一个[[聯邦咨询委员会|联邦咨询委员会]]，目的是推進 「[[愛國主義教育|愛國主義教育]] 」<ref>{{Cite web|title=拜登签令撤销特朗普此前成立加强爱国主义教育的“1776委员会”|url=https://finance.sina.com.cn/world/mzjj/2021-01-21/doc-ikftpnny0254291.shtml|accessdate=|author=|date=|format=|publisher=|language=|archive-date=2021-01-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210130074157/https://finance.sina.com.cn/world/mzjj/2021-01-21/doc-ikftpnny0254291.shtml}}</ref><ref name="NYTimes">{{Cite news|author=Crowley|first=Michael|author2=Schuessler|first2=Jennifer|date=2021-01-19|title=Trump's 1776 Commission Critiques Liberalism in Report Derided by Historians|language=en-US|work=The New York Times|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/18/us/politics/trump-1776-commission-report.html|accessdate=2021-01-19|issn=0362-4331|archive-date=2021-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210120003414/https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/18/us/politics/trump-1776-commission-report.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。不過美国历史方面的专业學者並沒有加入该委员会，在特朗普任期结束前两天，即2021年1月18日的[[马丁·路德·金纪念日|马丁·路德·金纪念日]]，1776委員會发布了《1776报告》（The 1776 Report）。该报告受到历史学家的强烈批评，历史学家称该报告为伪历史<ref name="WashingtonPost">{{Cite news|author=Gillian Brockell|first=|date=January 19, 2021|title='A hack job,' 'outright lies': Trump commission’s ‘1776 Report’ outrages historians|work=The Washington Post|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/history/2021/01/19/1776-report-historians-trump/|accessdate=|archive-date=2021-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210120170149/https://www.washingtonpost.com/history/2021/01/19/1776-report-historians-trump/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2021年1月20日，第46任美國總統[[乔·拜登|乔·拜登]]宣佈解散1776委員會 <ref name="Shear">{{Cite web|title=On Day 1, Biden Moves to Undo Trump's Legacy|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/20/us/politics/biden-executive-action.html|accessdate=January 20, 2021|author=Shear|date=January 20, 2021|first=Michael D.|authorlink=Michael D. Shear|work=[[New_York_Times|New York Times]]|archive-date=2021-01-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210120193829/https://www.nytimes.com/2021/01/20/us/politics/biden-executive-action.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing-room/presidential-actions/2021/01/20/executive-order-advancing-racial-equity-and-support-for-underserved-communities-through-the-federal-government/ |title=Executive Order On Advancing Racial Equity and Support for Underserved Communities Through the Federal Government |accessdate=2021-01-22 |archive-date=2021-01-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210121170355/https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing-room/presidential-actions/2021/01/20/executive-order-advancing-racial-equity-and-support-for-underserved-communities-through-the-federal-government/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

